All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BadItemException
Exception thrown when the program attempts to add an item of the incorrect implementing class of Packable to a Storage class.
Bag
A bag to store different personal items.
Book
A book that can be read.
Includes both fiction and non-fiction.
Box
A box to store different items in.
Boxes can be marked as fragile and have comments about their contents.
Clothes
Clothes owner by someone.
Clothes come in many types and sizes.
ClotheType
Enum to represent the size of various types of clothes in the simulation.
Furniture
Represents some household furniture that needs to be moved.
FurnitureType
Enum to represent the size of various different types of furniture in the simulation.
Laptop
A Laptop to do university work or gaming on.
MovingTruck
A moving truck to facilitate moving different items on a road.
Packable
Interface to represent any items that can be packed into a container.
PackingException
Exception thrown when an error occurs during the packing of a Storage class.
PackingOrderException
Exception thrown when the program attempts to add an items in the incorrect order.
Personal
Represents some personal item.
SimpleDisplay
A class to create and display a scenario managed by the MMS (Moving Management System).
Size
Enum to represent the size of various object's in the simulation.
Storage
Represents some form of storage entity.
StorageFullException
Exception thrown when the program attempts to add more items to storage than that particular storage unit can handle.
